result.formatted_address: 16 Lan Kwai Fong, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Tokio Joe

reviews.text:
Located in LKF this simple sushi and Japanese restaurant offers some interesting dishes. The fish quality is very good and the menu offers a lot of choices. Some sushi rolls have sometimes strange combinations like spicy tuna with bread flakes, my opinion is that the flakes are not really needed and even make the rolls taste less good than if they wouldn't put them.
But all in all a recommended place for that type of food in the area.
If you think you know what good sushi is, prepare to be blown away. I was impressed by how incredibly fresh and tasty the sushi is here. The service was stellar too.

Tables are pretty close to one another so there is little to no privacy for a business chat. Portions are decent, size wise and taste wise. Staff is polite and speaks good English. Drinks could be colder and specials could be priced better. It's a decent Japanese place but nothing special.

A popular Japanese restaurants for westerners or people working in Central. They specialise in sashimi or sushi. Fish very fresh and price is higher than an average Japanese restaurant but definitely not insane. Lunch set around HKD200. 
Less busy during weekends because it is located in the Lan Kwai Fong area.

This place has been around for 20+ years. They have loyal customers who come and just order chef's set (Omakase). But for those who are not big eaters you can orsrr a la carte. Go for sushi set. Fried rice and noodles are also good. They have a nice touch of giving you free tomato and edamame appetizers. Also yiu get some fruits at the end. Excellent service.
